      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HOPETOUN PARK (7) has been to the races 22 times without winning which is alarming, but that latest effort to finish just 1.1 lengths away over 1680m at Ipswich was full of merit. On a four-day back-up which is a positive lead from the stable. Worth the gamble at a decent price. NAMARA (3) recorded her seventh minor placing from 12 appearances when a closing second over 1540m on the Gold Coast Poly last time out. New to this trip but she finds the line well and is sure to receive an economical run from the good draw. TSZYUYA (4) stepped up sharply to a mile at Toowoomba most recently where she battled on well for a close fourth. A big drop in the weights brings her right into contention. MOMENT (5) is a one-paced filly who has only been to the races four times. Decent effort last time out at the Sunshine Coast. Not out of contention. CERTIFY (2) is bred to want this sort of trip and can improve second-up with the blinkers going on.",
